<subSubSection id="C3586572FF8AFFF70D3C1C88FDE2F94A" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36F9FF8AFFF70D3C1C88FF19FC27" blockId="7.[111,649,945,1700]" box="[113,213,945,971]" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36F9FF8AFFF70D3C1CE8FE0CFA89" blockId="7.[111,649,945,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">
The type is a fruiting specimen that was previously cited but not described in detail (Jacques-Félix 1985b: 36). In addition there are two recent collections including one (
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70C1D1B09FE32FBA4" box="[336,510,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">Stone et al. 2391</emphasis>
) with flower buds but no fully developed flowers. The prominently winged young branchlets of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF8AFFF70CAE1B56FD4BFB67" authorityName="R. D. Stone" authorityYear="2006" box="[483,647,1135,1161]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pterocladum">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70CAE1B56FD4BFB67" box="[483,647,1135,1161]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">M. pterocladum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble those seen in 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF8AFFF70C361BB6FD9CFB47" authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." box="[379,592,1167,1193]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capuronii">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70C361BB6FDC0FB47" box="[379,524,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">M. capuronii</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
-Fél., 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF8AFFF70D3E1B96FE4AFB27" authority="H. Perrier" authorityName="H. Perrier" box="[115,390,1199,1225]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pterocarpum">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70D3E1B96FED7FB27" box="[115,283,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">M. pterocarpum</emphasis>
H.Perrier
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF8AFFF70CF21B96FF64FB06" authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fernandesiorum">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70CF21B96FD4BFB27" box="[447,647,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">M. fernandesiorum</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
-Fél. The new species is also somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF8AFFF70DC11BD7FEA2FAE6" authority="H. Perrier" authorityName="H. Perrier" box="[140,366,1262,1288]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subsessile">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70DC11BD7FECAFAE6" box="[140,262,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">M. subsessile</emphasis>
H.Perrier
</taxonomicName>
, which notably differs in its slender, terete branchlets; papyriferous, short-petioled leaves that are smaller and strongly acuminate at the apex; and axillary cymes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36F9FF8AFFF70DC51A54FDE2F94A" blockId="7.[111,649,945,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">
A collection of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF8AFFF70C611A54FE3CFA69" box="[300,496,1389,1415]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichophyllum">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70C611A54FE3CFA69" box="[300,496,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">M. dolichophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70CB21A54FF7BFA48" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">Capuron SF- 28114</emphasis>
, P) from the 
<typeStatus id="54F9885BFF8AFFF70C0F1AB5FEBCFA48" box="[322,368,1420,1446]" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF8AFFF70CAE1AB5FD4BFA48" authorityName="R. D. Stone" authorityYear="2006" box="[483,647,1420,1446]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pterocladum">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70CAE1AB5FD4BFA48" box="[483,647,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">M. pterocladum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggests that the two species are at least partially sympatric. Their fruits are identical; they also resemble one another in having subcoriaceous leaves and cymes borne at the nodes below the current leaves. They are however quite different since 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF8AFFF70C8B1912FD4AF9AB" box="[454,646,1579,1605]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichophyllum">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF8AFFF70C8B1912FD4AF9AB" box="[454,646,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">M. dolichophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has petiolate leaves that are merely rounded (not cordate) at the base and with transverse veins oblique; its fruiting pedicels are also 
<quantity id="4CBA9B1CFF8AFFF70CD419B3FE3CF94A" box="[409,496,1674,1700]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3-4 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
